name: Save the MakeCorrections output
body: Use `corrections.save_output()` to save the output to a folder

name: v2.3.1
body:
1. Fix processing splitted PDFs
2. Support downloading BigFile

name: Fix OCR errors functionality
body:
- View your transactions processed in the last 24 hours
- Give user the ability to make character error corrections

name: User Control on Indices in the output
body: To provide user control on whether to output the row & column numbers in the output file

name: Feature: Corrections Made Easy
body:
**Data Cleaning** on the server output made easy with `MakeCorrections` class.
- split_merged_rows
- split_merged_columns
- fix_decimal_format
- fix_date_format functionalities

added `server_response` attribute to the session for easy reference

Update Google Colab Tutorial

Save tables to multiple sheets of a single excel file

`save_output` functionality in session to save Tables & Text output to local

Updated Tutorial in [example-code.ipynb](https://github.com/ExtractTable/ExtractTable-py/blob/master/example-code.ipynb)

name: Bug Fix: When processing big files
body: To handle `Invalid Object Exception` when processing big files

name: Bug Fix: Row & Column Indices
body:
#28 

- Maintain column and row indices order

- Display JobId & Wait message for async transactions

name: Support for API Key Plan Type outputs
body:
To support the below added features at API level
•	Tables + Text Data: non-tabular text along with the tabular data (when tables undetected, by default, response gets text data)
•	Text Accuracy Details: page level character accuracy details
•	Cell / Word Coordinates: x,y coordinates of all words and table's cell data
•	Cell / Word Level Accuracy: word level accuracy details
•	Non-English characters: for non-english alphabets like Mandrin, Japanese etc

name: v1.2.1.2
body: Fixed Columns were not in order in the output

name: Support URL as input
body: Support URL as input which downloads the file to the temporary directory for the instance, auto deleted on success

name: v1.0.1 - Stable Release
body: The first stable library to make it easier for python developers to use [ExtractTable](https://extracttable.com)'s API to extract tabular data (table) from images and scanned PDFs without worrying about table area, column regions, image rotation et al.
